{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1072,"text":"Chris Anderson: The rights of citizens,"},{"time":3083,"text":"the future of the Internet."},{"time":5169,"text":"So I would like to welcome to the TED stage"},{"time":8552,"text":"the man behind those revelations,"},{"time":11378,"text":"Ed Snowden."},{"time":13754,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":17321,"text":"Ed is in a remote location somewhere in Russia"},{"time":21574,"text":"controlling this bot from his laptop,"},{"time":24349,"text":"so he can see what the bot can see."},{"time":28402,"text":"Ed, welcome to the TED stage."},{"time":30350,"text":"What can you see, as a matter of fact?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":33961,"text":"Edward Snowden: Ha, I can see everyone."},{"time":35699,"text":"This is amazing."},{"time":37949,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":41162,"text":"CA: Ed, some questions for you."},{"time":44445,"text":"You've been called many things"},{"time":45738,"text":"in the last few months."},{"time":47303,"text":"You've been called a whistleblower, a traitor,"},{"time":52228,"text":"a hero."},{"time":53957,"text":"What words would you describe yourself with?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57774,"text":"ES: You know, everybody who is involved"},{"time":60436,"text":"with this debate"},{"time":61932,"text":"has been struggling over me and my personality"},{"time":64674,"text":"and how to describe me."},{"time":67723,"text":"But when I think about it,"},{"time":69412,"text":"this isn't the question that\nwe should be struggling with."},{"time":72841,"text":"Who I am really doesn't matter at all."},{"time":76008,"text":"If I'm the worst person in the world,"},{"time":78720,"text":"you can hate me and move on."},{"time":80677,"text":"What really matters here are the issues."},{"time":83212,"text":"What really matters here is the\nkind of government we want,"},{"time":86047,"text":"the kind of Internet we want,"},{"time":87560,"text":"the kind of relationship between people"},{"time":90118,"text":"and societies."},{"time":91458,"text":"And that's what I'm hoping\nthe debate will move towards,"},{"time":94546,"text":"and we've seen that increasing over time."},{"time":96918,"text":"If I had to describe myself,"},{"time":98828,"text":"I wouldn't use words like \"hero.\""},{"time":100172,"text":"I wouldn't use \"patriot,\" and I wouldn't use \"traitor.\""},{"time":102874,"text":"I'd say I'm an American and I'm a citizen,"},{"time":105068,"text":"just like everyone else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107632,"text":"CA: So just to give some context"},{"time":109505,"text":"for those who don't know the whole story --"},{"time":111701,"text":"(Applause) —"},{"time":115431,"text":"this time a year ago, you were stationed in Hawaii"},{"time":119994,"text":"working as a consultant to the NSA."},{"time":122384,"text":"As a sysadmin, you had access"},{"time":124428,"text":"to their systems,"},{"time":126833,"text":"and you began revealing\ncertain classified documents"},{"time":131087,"text":"to some handpicked journalists"},{"time":134287,"text":"leading the way to June's revelations."},{"time":135878,"text":"Now, what propelled you to do this?"},{"time":141254,"text":"ES: You know,"},{"time":144040,"text":"when I was sitting in Hawaii,"},{"time":146220,"text":"and the years before, when I was\nworking in the intelligence community,"},{"time":148878,"text":"I saw a lot of things that had disturbed me."},{"time":152600,"text":"We do a lot of good things\nin the intelligence community,"},{"time":155877,"text":"things that need to be done,"},{"time":157070,"text":"and things that help everyone."},{"time":159767,"text":"But there are also things that go too far."},{"time":161724,"text":"There are things that shouldn't be done,"},{"time":163020,"text":"and decisions that were being made in secret"},{"time":166088,"text":"without the public's awareness,"},{"time":167336,"text":"without the public's consent,"},{"time":169848,"text":"and without even our representatives in government"},{"time":172700,"text":"having knowledge of these programs."},{"time":176333,"text":"When I really came to struggle with these issues,"},{"time":180866,"text":"I thought to myself,"},{"time":182488,"text":"how can I do this in the most responsible way,"},{"time":185574,"text":"that maximizes the public benefit"},{"time":188582,"text":"while minimizing the risks?"},{"time":191293,"text":"And out of all the solutions that I could come up with,"},{"time":194381,"text":"out of going to Congress,"},{"time":196623,"text":"when there were no laws,"},{"time":197926,"text":"there were no legal protections"},{"time":199611,"text":"for a private employee,"},{"time":201378,"text":"a contractor in intelligence like myself,"},{"time":204711,"text":"there was a risk that I would be\nburied along with the information"},{"time":208358,"text":"and the public would never find out."},{"time":210265,"text":"But the First Amendment of\nthe United States Constitution"},{"time":213287,"text":"guarantees us a free press for a reason,"},{"time":216828,"text":"and that's to enable an adversarial press,"},{"time":220033,"text":"to challenge the government,"},{"time":221930,"text":"but also to work together with the government,"},{"time":224564,"text":"to have a dialogue and debate about how we can"},{"time":226882,"text":"inform the public about matters of vital importance"},{"time":232321,"text":"without putting our national security at risk."},{"time":235451,"text":"And by working with journalists,"},{"time":237127,"text":"by giving all of my information"},{"time":239281,"text":"back to the American people,"},{"time":241558,"text":"rather than trusting myself to make"},{"time":243329,"text":"the decisions about publication,"},{"time":246063,"text":"we've had a robust debate"},{"time":248299,"text":"with a deep investment by the government"},{"time":251566,"text":"that I think has resulted in a benefit for everyone."},{"time":256672,"text":"And the risks that have been threatened,"},{"time":260447,"text":"the risks that have been played up"},{"time":262580,"text":"by the government"},{"time":264132,"text":"have never materialized."},{"time":265558,"text":"We've never seen any evidence"},{"time":267636,"text":"of even a single instance of specific harm,"},{"time":271192,"text":"and because of that,"},{"time":272661,"text":"I'm comfortable with the decisions that I made."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274788,"text":"CA: So let me show the audience"},{"time":277001,"text":"a couple of examples of what you revealed."},{"time":279470,"text":"If we could have a slide up, and Ed,"},{"time":281382,"text":"I don't know whether you can see,"},{"time":283137,"text":"the slides are here."},{"time":284251,"text":"This is a slide of the PRISM program,"},{"time":286836,"text":"and maybe you could tell the audience"},{"time":289305,"text":"what that was that was revealed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291911,"text":"ES: The best way to understand PRISM,"},{"time":294123,"text":"because there's been a little bit of controversy,"},{"time":295584,"text":"is to first talk about what PRISM isn't."},{"time":299335,"text":"Much of the debate in the U.S.\nhas been about metadata."},{"time":302090,"text":"They've said it's just metadata, it's just metadata,"},{"time":304981,"text":"and they're talking about a specific legal authority"},{"time":307722,"text":"called Section 215 of the Patriot Act."},{"time":310427,"text":"That allows sort of a warrantless wiretapping,"},{"time":313496,"text":"mass surveillance of the entire country's"},{"time":315859,"text":"phone records, things like that --"},{"time":318016,"text":"who you're talking to,"},{"time":319378,"text":"when you're talking to them,"},{"time":321406,"text":"where you traveled."},{"time":322702,"text":"These are all metadata events."},{"time":325203,"text":"PRISM is about content."},{"time":328549,"text":"It's a program through which the government could"},{"time":330689,"text":"compel corporate America,"},{"time":332733,"text":"it could deputize corporate America"},{"time":336126,"text":"to do its dirty work for the NSA."},{"time":339990,"text":"And even though some of\nthese companies did resist,"},{"time":342986,"text":"even though some of them --"},{"time":344409,"text":"I believe Yahoo was one of them —"},{"time":345655,"text":"challenged them in court, they all lost,"},{"time":348312,"text":"because it was never tried by an open court."},{"time":351227,"text":"They were only tried by a secret court."},{"time":354358,"text":"And something that we've seen,"},{"time":355725,"text":"something about the PRISM program\nthat's very concerning to me is,"},{"time":358429,"text":"there's been a talking point in the U.S. government"},{"time":360408,"text":"where they've said 15 federal judges"},{"time":364159,"text":"have reviewed these programs\nand found them to be lawful,"},{"time":366857,"text":"but what they don't tell you"},{"time":369577,"text":"is those are secret judges"},{"time":372207,"text":"in a secret court"},{"time":374209,"text":"based on secret interpretations of law"},{"time":377283,"text":"that's considered 34,000 warrant requests"},{"time":381517,"text":"over 33 years,"},{"time":383976,"text":"and in 33 years only rejected"},{"time":386163,"text":"11 government requests."},{"time":389046,"text":"These aren't the people that we want deciding"},{"time":391793,"text":"what the role of corporate America"},{"time":393939,"text":"in a free and open Internet should be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396395,"text":"CA: Now, this slide that we're showing here"},{"time":398506,"text":"shows the dates in which"},{"time":400718,"text":"different technology companies, Internet companies,"},{"time":403133,"text":"are alleged to have joined the program,"},{"time":405487,"text":"and where data collection began from them."},{"time":408445,"text":"Now, they have denied collaborating with the NSA."},{"time":413194,"text":"How was that data collected by the NSA?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":418298,"text":"ES: Right. So the NSA's own slides"},{"time":421477,"text":"refer to it as direct access."},{"time":424277,"text":"What that means to an actual NSA analyst,"},{"time":427027,"text":"someone like me who was working\nas an intelligence analyst"},{"time":430135,"text":"targeting, Chinese cyber-hackers,"},{"time":432606,"text":"things like that, in Hawaii,"},{"time":434688,"text":"is the provenance of that data"},{"time":436657,"text":"is directly from their servers."},{"time":438913,"text":"It doesn't mean"},{"time":440977,"text":"that there's a group of company representatives"},{"time":443783,"text":"sitting in a smoky room with the NSA"},{"time":446220,"text":"palling around and making back-room deals"},{"time":448010,"text":"about how they're going to give this stuff away."},{"time":450553,"text":"Now each company handles it different ways."},{"time":452946,"text":"Some are responsible."},{"time":454122,"text":"Some are somewhat less responsible."},{"time":456213,"text":"But the bottom line is, when we talk about"},{"time":457981,"text":"how this information is given,"},{"time":461360,"text":"it's coming from the companies themselves."},{"time":463846,"text":"It's not stolen from the lines."},{"time":466141,"text":"But there's an important thing to remember here:"},{"time":468073,"text":"even though companies pushed back,"},{"time":470004,"text":"even though companies demanded,"},{"time":472057,"text":"hey, let's do this through a warrant process,"},{"time":474603,"text":"let's do this"},{"time":476377,"text":"where we actually have some sort of legal review,"},{"time":479526,"text":"some sort of basis for handing over"},{"time":481357,"text":"these users' data,"},{"time":483297,"text":"we saw stories in the Washington Post last year"},{"time":485688,"text":"that weren't as well reported as the PRISM story"},{"time":488900,"text":"that said the NSA broke in"},{"time":491499,"text":"to the data center communications"},{"time":493300,"text":"between Google to itself"},{"time":495456,"text":"and Yahoo to itself."},{"time":497034,"text":"So even these companies that are cooperating"},{"time":499866,"text":"in at least a compelled but hopefully lawful manner"},{"time":502737,"text":"with the NSA,"},{"time":504610,"text":"the NSA isn't satisfied with that,"},{"time":507906,"text":"and because of that, we need our companies"},{"time":509884,"text":"to work very hard"},{"time":512699,"text":"to guarantee that they're going to represent"},{"time":515171,"text":"the interests of the user, and also advocate"},{"time":517757,"text":"for the rights of the users."},{"time":519673,"text":"And I think over the last year,"},{"time":520947,"text":"we've seen the companies that are named"},{"time":522530,"text":"on the PRISM slides"},{"time":523948,"text":"take great strides to do that,"},{"time":525757,"text":"and I encourage them to continue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528010,"text":"CA: What more should they do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530692,"text":"ES: The biggest thing that an Internet company"},{"time":534209,"text":"in America can do today, right now,"},{"time":537435,"text":"without consulting with lawyers,"},{"time":538877,"text":"to protect the rights of users worldwide,"},{"time":542416,"text":"is to enable SSL web encryption"},{"time":547799,"text":"on every page you visit."},{"time":549804,"text":"The reason this matters is today,"},{"time":552746,"text":"if you go to look at a copy of \"1984\" on Amazon.com,"},{"time":557984,"text":"the NSA can see a record of that,"},{"time":560431,"text":"the Russian intelligence service\ncan see a record of that,"},{"time":562650,"text":"the Chinese service can see a record of that,"},{"time":565107,"text":"the French service, the German service,"},{"time":567005,"text":"the services of Andorra."},{"time":568327,"text":"They can all see it because it's unencrypted."},{"time":571605,"text":"The world's library is Amazon.com,"},{"time":575205,"text":"but not only do they not\nsupport encryption by default,"},{"time":577860,"text":"you cannot choose to use encryption"},{"time":580026,"text":"when browsing through books."},{"time":581753,"text":"This is something that we need to change,"},{"time":583462,"text":"not just for Amazon, I don't mean to single them out,"},{"time":585337,"text":"but they're a great example."},{"time":586829,"text":"All companies need to move"},{"time":588497,"text":"to an encrypted browsing habit by default"},{"time":591890,"text":"for all users who haven't taken any action"},{"time":594374,"text":"or picked any special methods on their own."},{"time":596635,"text":"That'll increase the privacy and the rights"},{"time":598946,"text":"that people enjoy worldwide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601711,"text":"CA: Ed, come with me to this part of the stage."},{"time":604189,"text":"I want to show you the next slide here. (Applause)"},{"time":607142,"text":"This is a program called Boundless Informant."},{"time":609850,"text":"What is that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":611526,"text":"ES: So, I've got to give credit to the NSA"},{"time":613706,"text":"for using appropriate names on this."},{"time":616149,"text":"This is one of my favorite NSA cryptonyms."},{"time":619994,"text":"Boundless Informant"},{"time":621464,"text":"is a program that the NSA hid from Congress."},{"time":624314,"text":"The NSA was previously asked by Congress,"},{"time":626723,"text":"was there any ability that they had"},{"time":628936,"text":"to even give a rough ballpark estimate"},{"time":632694,"text":"of the amount of American communications"},{"time":634880,"text":"that were being intercepted."},{"time":637014,"text":"They said no. They said, we don't track those stats,"},{"time":640045,"text":"and we can't track those stats."},{"time":641594,"text":"We can't tell you how many communications"},{"time":644698,"text":"we're intercepting around the world,"},{"time":646161,"text":"because to tell you that would be"},{"time":647648,"text":"to invade your privacy."},{"time":650955,"text":"Now, I really appreciate that sentiment from them,"},{"time":653170,"text":"but the reality, when you look at this slide is,"},{"time":655305,"text":"not only do they have the capability,"},{"time":656958,"text":"the capability already exists."},{"time":659574,"text":"It's already in place."},{"time":661248,"text":"The NSA has its own internal data format"},{"time":664396,"text":"that tracks both ends of a communication,"},{"time":668545,"text":"and if it says,"},{"time":669827,"text":"this communication came from America,"},{"time":671853,"text":"they can tell Congress how\nmany of those communications"},{"time":674209,"text":"they have today, right now."},{"time":676725,"text":"And what Boundless Informant tells us"},{"time":679696,"text":"is more communications are being intercepted"},{"time":682422,"text":"in America about Americans"},{"time":685395,"text":"than there are in Russia about Russians."},{"time":688815,"text":"I'm not sure that's what an intelligence agency"},{"time":690680,"text":"should be aiming for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692999,"text":"CA: Ed, there was a story broken\nin the Washington Post,"},{"time":695405,"text":"again from your data."},{"time":697127,"text":"The headline says,"},{"time":698806,"text":"\"NSA broke privacy rules"},{"time":700303,"text":"thousands of times per year.\""},{"time":702333,"text":"Tell us about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703871,"text":"ES: We also heard in Congressional\ntestimony last year,"},{"time":706464,"text":"it was an amazing thing for someone like me"},{"time":708401,"text":"who came from the NSA"},{"time":710105,"text":"and who's seen the actual internal documents,"},{"time":712677,"text":"knows what's in them,"},{"time":715268,"text":"to see officials testifying under oath"},{"time":717808,"text":"that there had been no abuses,"},{"time":719690,"text":"that there had been no violations of the NSA's rules,"},{"time":723323,"text":"when we knew this story was coming."},{"time":726264,"text":"But what's especially interesting about this,"},{"time":728352,"text":"about the fact that the NSA has violated"},{"time":730400,"text":"their own rules, their own laws"},{"time":732768,"text":"thousands of times in a single year,"},{"time":735441,"text":"including one event by itself,"},{"time":738168,"text":"one event out of those 2,776,"},{"time":743144,"text":"that affected more than 3,000 people."},{"time":745450,"text":"In another event, they intercepted"},{"time":747289,"text":"all the calls in Washington, D.C., by accident."},{"time":751501,"text":"What's amazing about this,"},{"time":753738,"text":"this report, that didn't get that much attention,"},{"time":755946,"text":"is the fact that not only were there 2,776 abuses,"},{"time":760807,"text":"the chairman of the Senate Intelligence Committee,"},{"time":762948,"text":"Dianne Feinstein, had not seen this report"},{"time":766935,"text":"until the Washington Post contacted her"},{"time":770126,"text":"asking for comment on the report."},{"time":772574,"text":"And she then requested a copy from the NSA"},{"time":774467,"text":"and received it,"},{"time":776168,"text":"but had never seen this before that."},{"time":778195,"text":"What does that say about the state of oversight"},{"time":780882,"text":"in American intelligence"},{"time":782619,"text":"when the chairman of the\nSenate Intelligence Committee"},{"time":784407,"text":"has no idea that the rules are being broken"},{"time":787200,"text":"thousands of times every year?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":789360,"text":"CA: Ed, one response to this whole debate is this:"},{"time":792989,"text":"Why should we care about"},{"time":795654,"text":"all this surveillance, honestly?"},{"time":797122,"text":"I mean, look, if you've done nothing wrong,"},{"time":799274,"text":"you've got nothing to worry about."},{"time":802058,"text":"What's wrong with that point of view?"},{"time":804350,"text":"ES: Well, so the first thing is,"},{"time":805998,"text":"you're giving up your rights."},{"time":807711,"text":"You're saying hey, you know,"},{"time":809069,"text":"I don't think I'm going to need them,"},{"time":811441,"text":"so I'm just going to trust that, you know,"},{"time":813123,"text":"let's get rid of them, it doesn't really matter,"},{"time":816101,"text":"these guys are going to do the right thing."},{"time":818075,"text":"Your rights matter"},{"time":819934,"text":"because you never know when\nyou're going to need them."},{"time":822776,"text":"Beyond that, it's a part of our cultural identity,"},{"time":825058,"text":"not just in America,"},{"time":827190,"text":"but in Western societies"},{"time":828781,"text":"and in democratic societies around the world."},{"time":831743,"text":"People should be able to pick up the phone"},{"time":834147,"text":"and to call their family,"},{"time":835601,"text":"people should be able to send a text message"},{"time":837600,"text":"to their loved ones,"},{"time":838728,"text":"people should be able to buy a book online,"},{"time":841182,"text":"they should be able to travel by train,"},{"time":842972,"text":"they should be able to buy an airline ticket"},{"time":845189,"text":"without wondering about how these events"},{"time":846926,"text":"are going to look to an agent of the government,"},{"time":850611,"text":"possibly not even your government"},{"time":853201,"text":"years in the future,"},{"time":854956,"text":"how they're going to be misinterpreted"},{"time":856696,"text":"and what they're going to think your intentions were."},{"time":859480,"text":"We have a right to privacy."},{"time":861554,"text":"We require warrants to be based on probable cause"},{"time":865172,"text":"or some kind of individualized suspicion"},{"time":867636,"text":"because we recognize that trusting anybody,"},{"time":872163,"text":"any government authority,"},{"time":873757,"text":"with the entirety of human communications"},{"time":876841,"text":"in secret and without oversight"},{"time":879274,"text":"is simply too great a temptation to be ignored."}]},{"cues":[{"time":884118,"text":"CA: Some people are furious at what you've done."},{"time":886677,"text":"I heard a quote recently from Dick Cheney"},{"time":889516,"text":"who said that Julian Assange was a flea bite,"},{"time":895408,"text":"Edward Snowden is the lion\nthat bit the head off the dog."},{"time":898830,"text":"He thinks you've committed"},{"time":900383,"text":"one of the worst acts of betrayal"},{"time":902675,"text":"in American history."},{"time":904781,"text":"What would you say to people who think that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":910975,"text":"ES: Dick Cheney's really something else."},{"time":913180,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":920476,"text":"Thank you. (Laughter)"},{"time":925378,"text":"I think it's amazing, because at the time"},{"time":927854,"text":"Julian Assange was doing some of his greatest work,"},{"time":931629,"text":"Dick Cheney was saying"},{"time":933065,"text":"he was going to end governments worldwide,"},{"time":935495,"text":"the skies were going to ignite"},{"time":938400,"text":"and the seas were going to boil off,"},{"time":940536,"text":"and now he's saying it's a flea bite."},{"time":942754,"text":"So we should be suspicious about the same sort of"},{"time":945267,"text":"overblown claims of damage to national security"},{"time":949460,"text":"from these kind of officials."},{"time":951145,"text":"But let's assume that these\npeople really believe this."},{"time":957994,"text":"I would argue that they have kind of"},{"time":960224,"text":"a narrow conception of national security."},{"time":964594,"text":"The prerogatives of people like Dick Cheney"},{"time":967841,"text":"do not keep the nation safe."},{"time":970822,"text":"The public interest is not always the same"},{"time":974855,"text":"as the national interest."},{"time":977290,"text":"Going to war with people who are not our enemy"},{"time":981184,"text":"in places that are not a threat"},{"time":983314,"text":"doesn't make us safe,"},{"time":985481,"text":"and that applies whether it's in Iraq"},{"time":987648,"text":"or on the Internet."},{"time":989415,"text":"The Internet is not the enemy."},{"time":990938,"text":"Our economy is not the enemy."},{"time":992963,"text":"American businesses, Chinese businesses,"},{"time":995249,"text":"and any other company out there"},{"time":999820,"text":"is a part of our society."},{"time":1002251,"text":"It's a part of our interconnected world."},{"time":1004465,"text":"There are ties of fraternity that bond us together,"},{"time":1008910,"text":"and if we destroy these bonds"},{"time":1011578,"text":"by undermining the standards, the security,"},{"time":1014733,"text":"the manner of behavior,"},{"time":1017590,"text":"that nations and citizens all around the world"},{"time":1020541,"text":"expect us to abide by."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022918,"text":"CA: But it's alleged that you've stolen"},{"time":1026620,"text":"1.7 million documents."},{"time":1028519,"text":"It seems only a few hundred of them"},{"time":1030346,"text":"have been shared with journalists so far."},{"time":1033203,"text":"Are there more revelations to come?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036248,"text":"ES: There are absolutely more revelations to come."},{"time":1038690,"text":"I don't think there's any question"},{"time":1041491,"text":"that some of the most important reporting"},{"time":1045738,"text":"to be done is yet to come."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050478,"text":"CA: Come here, because I want to ask you"},{"time":1052540,"text":"about this particular revelation."},{"time":1054067,"text":"Come and take a look at this."},{"time":1057089,"text":"I mean, this is a story which I think\nfor a lot of the techies in this room"},{"time":1060337,"text":"is the single most shocking thing"},{"time":1062076,"text":"that they have heard in the last few months."},{"time":1064436,"text":"It's about a program called \"Bullrun.\""},{"time":1067061,"text":"Can you explain what that is?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1070837,"text":"ES: So Bullrun, and this is again"},{"time":1072545,"text":"where we've got to thank the NSA for their candor,"},{"time":1079642,"text":"this is a program named after a Civil War battle."},{"time":1084232,"text":"The British counterpart is called Edgehill,"},{"time":1085845,"text":"which is a U.K. civil war battle."},{"time":1087320,"text":"And the reason that I believe they're named this way"},{"time":1089527,"text":"is because they target our own infrastructure."},{"time":1093016,"text":"They're programs through which the NSA"},{"time":1095707,"text":"intentionally misleads corporate partners."},{"time":1099922,"text":"They tell corporate partners that these"},{"time":1101804,"text":"are safe standards."},{"time":1103479,"text":"They say hey, we need to work with you"},{"time":1105498,"text":"to secure your systems,"},{"time":1109151,"text":"but in reality, they're giving bad advice"},{"time":1112344,"text":"to these companies that makes them"},{"time":1113610,"text":"degrade the security of their services."},{"time":1115905,"text":"They're building in backdoors that not only"},{"time":1118234,"text":"the NSA can exploit,"},{"time":1120592,"text":"but anyone else who has time and money"},{"time":1123113,"text":"to research and find it"},{"time":1125233,"text":"can then use to let themselves in"},{"time":1127367,"text":"to the world's communications."},{"time":1129237,"text":"And this is really dangerous,"},{"time":1131007,"text":"because if we lose a single standard,"},{"time":1135191,"text":"if we lose the trust of something like SSL,"},{"time":1138250,"text":"which was specifically targeted"},{"time":1139732,"text":"by the Bullrun program,"},{"time":1141855,"text":"we will live a less safe world overall."},{"time":1144523,"text":"We won't be able to access our banks"},{"time":1146630,"text":"and we won't be able to access commerce"},{"time":1151883,"text":"without worrying about people\nmonitoring those communications"},{"time":1154706,"text":"or subverting them for their own ends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1156884,"text":"CA: And do those same decisions also potentially"},{"time":1160953,"text":"open America up to cyberattacks"},{"time":1163939,"text":"from other sources?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1167855,"text":"ES: Absolutely."},{"time":1169320,"text":"One of the problems,"},{"time":1171052,"text":"one of the dangerous legacies"},{"time":1174502,"text":"that we've seen in the post-9/11 era,"},{"time":1177994,"text":"is that the NSA has traditionally worn two hats."},{"time":1182231,"text":"They've been in charge of offensive operations,"},{"time":1184157,"text":"that is hacking,"},{"time":1185278,"text":"but they've also been in\ncharge of defensive operations,"},{"time":1187988,"text":"and traditionally they've always prioritized"},{"time":1190351,"text":"defense over offense"},{"time":1191738,"text":"based on the principle"},{"time":1193128,"text":"that American secrets are simply worth more."},{"time":1195944,"text":"If we hack a Chinese business"},{"time":1198054,"text":"and steal their secrets,"},{"time":1199738,"text":"if we hack a government office in Berlin"},{"time":1201821,"text":"and steal their secrets,"},{"time":1203919,"text":"that has less value to the American people"},{"time":1207526,"text":"than making sure that the Chinese"},{"time":1209626,"text":"can't get access to our secrets."},{"time":1212132,"text":"So by reducing the security of our communications,"},{"time":1216263,"text":"they're not only putting the world at risk,"},{"time":1218291,"text":"they're putting America at risk in a fundamental way,"},{"time":1220563,"text":"because intellectual property is the basis,"},{"time":1223234,"text":"the foundation of our economy,"},{"time":1225161,"text":"and if we put that at risk through weak security,"},{"time":1227419,"text":"we're going to be paying for it for years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1229048,"text":"CA: But they've made a calculation"},{"time":1230595,"text":"that it was worth doing this"},{"time":1232786,"text":"as part of America's defense against terrorism."},{"time":1236325,"text":"Surely that makes it a price worth paying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1239937,"text":"ES: Well, when you look at the results"},{"time":1243824,"text":"of these programs in stopping terrorism,"},{"time":1246131,"text":"you will see that that's unfounded,"},{"time":1249881,"text":"and you don't have to take my word for it,"},{"time":1251800,"text":"because we've had the first open court,"},{"time":1255572,"text":"the first federal court that's reviewed this,"},{"time":1257941,"text":"outside the secrecy arrangement,"},{"time":1260737,"text":"called these programs Orwellian"},{"time":1262724,"text":"and likely unconstitutional."},{"time":1264958,"text":"Congress, who has access"},{"time":1267697,"text":"to be briefed on these things,"},{"time":1269008,"text":"and now has the desire to be,"},{"time":1271990,"text":"has produced bills to reform it,"},{"time":1274397,"text":"and two independent White House panels"},{"time":1277282,"text":"who reviewed all of the classified evidence"},{"time":1279372,"text":"said these programs have never stopped"},{"time":1282005,"text":"a single terrorist attack"},{"time":1283766,"text":"that was imminent in the United States."},{"time":1287269,"text":"So is it really terrorism that we're stopping?"},{"time":1290455,"text":"Do these programs have any value at all?"},{"time":1292786,"text":"I say no, and all three branches"},{"time":1295030,"text":"of the American government say no as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1297462,"text":"CA: I mean, do you think there's a deeper motivation"},{"time":1299275,"text":"for them than the war against terrorism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1302560,"text":"ES: I'm sorry, I couldn't hear you, say again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1304110,"text":"CA: Sorry. Do you think there's a deeper motivation"},{"time":1307110,"text":"for them other than the war against terrorism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1310989,"text":"ES: Yeah. The bottom line is that terrorism"},{"time":1313684,"text":"has always been what we in the intelligence world"},{"time":1315885,"text":"would call a cover for action."},{"time":1319158,"text":"Terrorism is something that provokes"},{"time":1321083,"text":"an emotional response that allows people"},{"time":1323313,"text":"to rationalize authorizing powers and programs"},{"time":1327670,"text":"that they wouldn't give otherwise."},{"time":1330114,"text":"The Bullrun and Edgehill-type programs,"},{"time":1332600,"text":"the NSA asked for these authorities"},{"time":1334317,"text":"back in the 1990s."},{"time":1336254,"text":"They asked the FBI to go to\nCongress and make the case."},{"time":1339244,"text":"The FBI went to Congress and did make the case."},{"time":1341418,"text":"But Congress and the American people said no."},{"time":1343983,"text":"They said, it's not worth the risk to our economy."},{"time":1346394,"text":"They said it's worth too much damage"},{"time":1348313,"text":"to our society to justify the gains."},{"time":1351000,"text":"But what we saw is, in the post-9/11 era,"},{"time":1355275,"text":"they used secrecy and they\nused the justification of terrorism"},{"time":1358526,"text":"to start these programs in secret"},{"time":1360460,"text":"without asking Congress,"},{"time":1362272,"text":"without asking the American people,"},{"time":1364452,"text":"and it's that kind of government behind closed doors"},{"time":1367190,"text":"that we need to guard ourselves against,"},{"time":1369749,"text":"because it makes us less safe,"},{"time":1370999,"text":"and it offers no value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1372891,"text":"CA: Okay, come with me here for a sec,"},{"time":1374757,"text":"because I've got a more personal question for you."},{"time":1376939,"text":"Speaking of terror,"},{"time":1379863,"text":"most people would find the\nsituation you're in right now"},{"time":1383820,"text":"in Russia pretty terrifying."},{"time":1387116,"text":"You obviously heard what happened,"},{"time":1390703,"text":"what the treatment that Bradley Manning got,"},{"time":1392896,"text":"Chelsea Manning as now is,"},{"time":1395177,"text":"and there was a story in Buzzfeed saying that"},{"time":1397664,"text":"there are people in the intelligence community"},{"time":1399322,"text":"who want you dead."},{"time":1401601,"text":"How are you coping with this?"},{"time":1403541,"text":"How are you coping with the fear?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1405490,"text":"ES: It's no mystery"},{"time":1408494,"text":"that there are governments out\nthere that want to see me dead."},{"time":1414142,"text":"I've made clear again and again and again"},{"time":1417552,"text":"that I go to sleep every morning"},{"time":1420918,"text":"thinking about what I can\ndo for the American people."},{"time":1425478,"text":"I don't want to harm my government."},{"time":1428510,"text":"I want to help my government,"},{"time":1431773,"text":"but the fact that they are willing to"},{"time":1435581,"text":"completely ignore due process,"},{"time":1437901,"text":"they're willing to declare guilt"},{"time":1440609,"text":"without ever seeing a trial,"},{"time":1443895,"text":"these are things that we need to work against"},{"time":1446311,"text":"as a society, and say hey, this is not appropriate."},{"time":1449889,"text":"We shouldn't be threatening dissidents."},{"time":1451716,"text":"We shouldn't be criminalizing journalism."},{"time":1454730,"text":"And whatever part I can do to see that end,"},{"time":1458049,"text":"I'm happy to do despite the risks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1461202,"text":"CA: So I'd actually like to get some feedback"},{"time":1462726,"text":"from the audience here,"},{"time":1463945,"text":"because I know there's widely differing reactions"},{"time":1466049,"text":"to Edward Snowden."},{"time":1467990,"text":"Suppose you had the following two choices, right?"},{"time":1470278,"text":"You could view what he did"},{"time":1473084,"text":"as fundamentally a reckless act"},{"time":1474978,"text":"that has endangered America"},{"time":1478197,"text":"or you could view it as fundamentally a heroic act"},{"time":1481760,"text":"that will work towards America and the world's"},{"time":1485235,"text":"long-term good?"},{"time":1486622,"text":"Those are the two choices I'll give you."},{"time":1489940,"text":"I'm curious to see who's willing to vote with"},{"time":1492095,"text":"the first of those,"},{"time":1493512,"text":"that this was a reckless act?"},{"time":1496921,"text":"There are some hands going up."},{"time":1498576,"text":"Some hands going up."},{"time":1499960,"text":"It's hard to put your hand up"},{"time":1501236,"text":"when the man is standing right here,"},{"time":1503347,"text":"but I see them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1504912,"text":"ES: I can see you. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1507443,"text":"CA: And who goes with the second choice,"},{"time":1509704,"text":"the fundamentally heroic act?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1511587,"text":"(Applause) (Cheers)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1514234,"text":"And I think it's true to say that\nthere are a lot of people"},{"time":1516808,"text":"who didn't show a hand and I think"},{"time":1519033,"text":"are still thinking this through,"},{"time":1520743,"text":"because it seems to me that the debate around you"},{"time":1524201,"text":"doesn't split along traditional political lines."},{"time":1527310,"text":"It's not left or right, it's not really about"},{"time":1529564,"text":"pro-government, libertarian, or not just that."},{"time":1533686,"text":"Part of it is almost a generational issue."},{"time":1536399,"text":"You're part of a generation that grew up"},{"time":1538207,"text":"with the Internet, and it seems as if"},{"time":1541133,"text":"you become offended at almost a visceral level"},{"time":1544341,"text":"when you see something done"},{"time":1545637,"text":"that you think will harm the Internet."},{"time":1547699,"text":"Is there some truth to that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1551272,"text":"ES: It is. I think it's very true."},{"time":1556320,"text":"This is not a left or right issue."},{"time":1559418,"text":"Our basic freedoms, and when I say our,"},{"time":1561995,"text":"I don't just mean Americans,"},{"time":1563542,"text":"I mean people around the world,"},{"time":1565555,"text":"it's not a partisan issue."},{"time":1567901,"text":"These are things that all people believe,"},{"time":1569940,"text":"and it's up to all of us to protect them,"},{"time":1572465,"text":"and to people who have seen and enjoyed"},{"time":1575297,"text":"a free and open Internet,"},{"time":1576958,"text":"it's up to us to preserve that liberty"},{"time":1580184,"text":"for the next generation to enjoy,"},{"time":1582089,"text":"and if we don't change things,"},{"time":1583954,"text":"if we don't stand up to make the changes"},{"time":1587087,"text":"we need to do to keep the Internet safe,"},{"time":1590294,"text":"not just for us but for everyone,"},{"time":1593062,"text":"we're going to lose that,"},{"time":1594527,"text":"and that would be a tremendous loss,"},{"time":1595780,"text":"not just for us, but for the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1598127,"text":"CA: Well, I have heard similar language recently"},{"time":1600200,"text":"from the founder of the world wide web,"},{"time":1602048,"text":"who I actually think is with us, Sir Tim Berners-Lee."},{"time":1606565,"text":"Tim, actually, would you like to come up and say,"},{"time":1609269,"text":"do we have a microphone for Tim?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1611140,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1613507,"text":"Tim, good to see you. Come up there."},{"time":1620582,"text":"Which camp are you in, by the way,"},{"time":1623019,"text":"traitor, hero? I have a theory on this, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1626519,"text":"Tim Berners-Lee: I've given much longer"},{"time":1629213,"text":"answers to that question, but hero,"},{"time":1632268,"text":"if I have to make the choice between the two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1635670,"text":"CA: And Ed, I think you've read"},{"time":1639003,"text":"the proposal that Sir Tim has talked about"},{"time":1641087,"text":"about a new Magna Carta to take back the Internet."},{"time":1644055,"text":"Is that something that makes sense?"},{"time":1646157,"text":"ES: Absolutely. I mean, my generation, I grew up"},{"time":1649798,"text":"not just thinking about the Internet,"},{"time":1651857,"text":"but I grew up in the Internet,"},{"time":1654221,"text":"and although I never expected to have the chance"},{"time":1658881,"text":"to defend it in such a direct and practical manner"},{"time":1664428,"text":"and to embody it in this unusual,"},{"time":1668224,"text":"almost avatar manner,"},{"time":1670353,"text":"I think there's something poetic about the fact that"},{"time":1673059,"text":"one of the sons of the Internet"},{"time":1675041,"text":"has actually become close to the Internet"},{"time":1678093,"text":"as a result of their political expression."},{"time":1680579,"text":"And I believe that a Magna Carta for the Internet"},{"time":1684290,"text":"is exactly what we need."},{"time":1686252,"text":"We need to encode our values"},{"time":1689760,"text":"not just in writing but in the structure of the Internet,"},{"time":1693107,"text":"and it's something that I hope,"},{"time":1695347,"text":"I invite everyone in the audience,"},{"time":1697870,"text":"not just here in Vancouver but around the world,"},{"time":1701120,"text":"to join and participate in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1703476,"text":"CA: Do you have a question for Ed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1705790,"text":"TBL: Well, two questions,"},{"time":1707820,"text":"a general question —"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1708944,"text":"CA: Ed, can you still hear us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1710739,"text":"ES: Yes, I can hear you.\nCA: Oh, he's back.\n"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1714255,"text":"TBL: The wiretap on your line"},{"time":1715850,"text":"got a little interfered with for a moment."},{"time":1717756,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1719409,"text":"ES: It's a little bit of an NSA problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1721611,"text":"TBL: So, from the 25 years,"},{"time":1725418,"text":"stepping back and thinking,"},{"time":1728355,"text":"what would you think would be"},{"time":1730101,"text":"the best that we could achieve"},{"time":1732708,"text":"from all the discussions that we have"},{"time":1734568,"text":"about the web we want?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1737461,"text":"ES: When we think about"},{"time":1740833,"text":"in terms of how far we can go,"},{"time":1743946,"text":"I think that's a question that's really only limited"},{"time":1746099,"text":"by what we're willing to put into it."},{"time":1748636,"text":"I think the Internet that we've enjoyed in the past"},{"time":1751593,"text":"has been exactly what we as not just a nation"},{"time":1757151,"text":"but as a people around the world need,"},{"time":1760490,"text":"and by cooperating, by engaging not just"},{"time":1764716,"text":"the technical parts of society,"},{"time":1766120,"text":"but as you said, the users,"},{"time":1768962,"text":"the people around the world who contribute"},{"time":1771026,"text":"through the Internet, through social media,"},{"time":1773468,"text":"who just check the weather,"},{"time":1775195,"text":"who rely on it every day as a part of their life,"},{"time":1777748,"text":"to champion that."},{"time":1780688,"text":"We'll get not just the Internet we've had,"},{"time":1783225,"text":"but a better Internet, a better now,"},{"time":1786174,"text":"something that we can use to build a future"},{"time":1790217,"text":"that'll be better not just than what we hoped for"},{"time":1793185,"text":"but anything that we could have imagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1795570,"text":"CA: It's 30 years ago that TED was founded, 1984."},{"time":1801032,"text":"A lot of the conversation since then has been"},{"time":1803037,"text":"along the lines that"},{"time":1805091,"text":"actually George Orwell got it wrong."},{"time":1806994,"text":"It's not Big Brother watching us."},{"time":1808713,"text":"We, through the power of the web,"},{"time":1810327,"text":"and transparency, are now watching Big Brother."},{"time":1812691,"text":"Your revelations kind of drove a stake"},{"time":1814952,"text":"through the heart of that rather optimistic view,"},{"time":1818699,"text":"but you still believe there's a way of doing something"},{"time":1822119,"text":"about that."},{"time":1823988,"text":"And you do too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1825728,"text":"ES: Right, so there is an argument to be made"},{"time":1831896,"text":"that the powers of Big Brother\nhave increased enormously."},{"time":1835493,"text":"There was a recent legal article at Yale"},{"time":1839822,"text":"that established something called\nthe Bankston-Soltani Principle,"},{"time":1843553,"text":"which is that our expectation of privacy is violated"},{"time":1848782,"text":"when the capabilities of government surveillance"},{"time":1850651,"text":"have become cheaper by an order of magnitude,"},{"time":1853846,"text":"and each time that occurs, we need to revisit"},{"time":1856568,"text":"and rebalance our privacy rights."},{"time":1859621,"text":"Now, that hasn't happened since"},{"time":1861611,"text":"the government's surveillance powers"},{"time":1863709,"text":"have increased by several orders of magnitude,"},{"time":1866489,"text":"and that's why we're in the\nproblem that we're in today,"},{"time":1869463,"text":"but there is still hope,"},{"time":1873275,"text":"because the power of individuals"},{"time":1875411,"text":"have also been increased by technology."},{"time":1878018,"text":"I am living proof"},{"time":1880019,"text":"that an individual can go head to head"},{"time":1882181,"text":"against the most powerful adversaries"},{"time":1884499,"text":"and the most powerful intelligence agencies"},{"time":1886820,"text":"around the world and win,"},{"time":1890580,"text":"and I think that's something"},{"time":1892240,"text":"that we need to take hope from,"},{"time":1894663,"text":"and we need to build on"},{"time":1895840,"text":"to make it accessible not just to technical experts"},{"time":1898277,"text":"but to ordinary citizens around the world."},{"time":1900794,"text":"Journalism is not a crime,"},{"time":1902461,"text":"communication is not a crime,"},{"time":1904251,"text":"and we should not be monitored\nin our everyday activities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1907195,"text":"CA: I'm not quite sure how\nyou shake the hand of a bot,"},{"time":1909924,"text":"but I imagine it's, this is the hand right here.\nTBL: That'll come very soon."},{"time":1915814,"text":"ES: Nice to meet you,"},{"time":1916937,"text":"and I hope my beam looks as nice"},{"time":1918984,"text":"as my view of you guys does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1921328,"text":"CA: Thank you, Tim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1924048,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1929780,"text":"I mean, The New York Times\nrecently called for an amnesty for you."},{"time":1933832,"text":"Would you welcome the chance\nto come back to America?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1938058,"text":"ES: Absolutely. There's really no question,"},{"time":1941943,"text":"the principles that have been the foundation"},{"time":1944525,"text":"of this project"},{"time":1946918,"text":"have been the public interest"},{"time":1950998,"text":"and the principles that underly"},{"time":1953941,"text":"the journalistic establishment in the United States"},{"time":1957217,"text":"and around the world,"},{"time":1959663,"text":"and I think if the press is now saying,"},{"time":1964508,"text":"we support this,"},{"time":1966590,"text":"this is something that needed to happen,"},{"time":1968678,"text":"that's a powerful argument,\nbut it's not the final argument,"},{"time":1971322,"text":"and I think that's something\nthat public should decide."},{"time":1974035,"text":"But at the same time,"},{"time":1975877,"text":"the government has hinted that they want"},{"time":1977423,"text":"some kind of deal,"},{"time":1979267,"text":"that they want me to compromise"},{"time":1981381,"text":"the journalists with which I've been working,"},{"time":1983556,"text":"to come back,"},{"time":1984989,"text":"and I want to make it very clear"},{"time":1987542,"text":"that I did not do this to be safe."},{"time":1990268,"text":"I did this to do what was right,"},{"time":1992536,"text":"and I'm not going to stop my work"},{"time":1994763,"text":"in the public interest"},{"time":1996137,"text":"just to benefit myself."},{"time":1998926,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2004704,"text":"CA: In the meantime,"},{"time":2006623,"text":"courtesy of the Internet and this technology,"},{"time":2010391,"text":"you're here, back in North America,"},{"time":2012041,"text":"not quite the U.S., Canada, in this form."},{"time":2016057,"text":"I'm curious, how does that feel?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2020951,"text":"ES: Canada is different than what I expected."},{"time":2023089,"text":"It's a lot warmer."},{"time":2025214,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":2030921,"text":"CA: At TED, the mission is \"ideas worth spreading.\""},{"time":2034177,"text":"If you could encapsulate it in a single idea,"},{"time":2036375,"text":"what is your idea worth spreading"},{"time":2038590,"text":"right now at this moment?"},{"time":2042665,"text":"ES: I would say the last year has been a reminder"},{"time":2046315,"text":"that democracy may die behind closed doors,"},{"time":2049918,"text":"but we as individuals are born"},{"time":2051822,"text":"behind those same closed doors,"},{"time":2054471,"text":"and we don't have to give up"},{"time":2056836,"text":"our privacy to have good government."},{"time":2060069,"text":"We don't have to give up our liberty"},{"time":2062159,"text":"to have security."},{"time":2063938,"text":"And I think by working together"},{"time":2066726,"text":"we can have both open government"},{"time":2069051,"text":"and private lives,"},{"time":2070988,"text":"and I look forward to working with everyone"},{"time":2072761,"text":"around the world to see that happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2075300,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2076638,"text":"CA: Ed, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2078878,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}